
Overview of noun bridle

The noun bridle has 2 senses (first 1 from tagged texts)
                                         
1. (4) bridle -- (headgear for a horse; includes a headstall and bit and reins to give the rider or driver control)
2. bridle, check, curb -- (the act of restraining power or action or limiting excess; "his common sense is a bridle to his quick temper")

Overview of verb bridle

The verb bridle has 3 senses (no senses from tagged texts)
                                       
1. bridle -- (anger or take offense; "She bridled at his suggestion to elope")
2. bridle -- (put a bridle on; "bridle horses")
3. bridle -- (respond to the reins, as of horses)
